xWnS17JRqB2Cjdgfncnnng
Been here twice now and, overall, I'm a fan. They do a good job getting the pizza out quickly but at the right temperature (smart that they use thin crust only). They make sure to know in advance what you're going to put on the pizza so they don't overload it. Price is good.  I do agree with some of the reviews, though, that their system for keeping track of everything needs work. I've only been here when there aren't many people, but I can't imagine that having the cashier write down everything on your pizza as you order it is the best way to go.  As an aside, when I was here I overheard the owner/manager talking with someone who seemed like a regular. At one point one of them commented: "This is pretty smart. If you don't like your pizza, you only have yourself to blame." I have to say that I kind of agree.

